rComments: Prof Green is great, cares, and wants student to succeed! He gave practice questions every lecture and went over them thoroughly & uses some of them in the midterm & exam;) He responds to questions/ emails quickly and answers questions on the class gc. The course is lecture heavy so study ahead and pay attention to graphs/ pictures on his slides.

Prof. Green cares about his students and wants them to succeed. He mentions his dog almost every lecture which is very cute. It is a very heavy material course but he gives review question that come in the exam/ midterm. Def a gem in uOttawa!

He is so sweet, and actually cares and tries to make things interesting. He gives practice questions to review, review sessions before exams, and even was in our class group chat. He also let us choose 2 topics that he lectured on. Don't get me wrong, you still gotta study ahead of time because it is very content heavy... Anki is your friend :)
